news.title: Nashik civic body Rs 15 crore short of its property tax target
news.para: Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC)’s commissioner, Chandrakant Pulkundwar, has directed the officials concerned to approach the defaulters directly and mobilize at least Rs 15-20 crore during the remaining days of the current fiscal.

news.title: Parliamentary panel raises concern over govt's over-emphasis on building house on land under PMAY-U
news.para: It said the over-emphasis on BLC vertical “diluted the objective” of reducing the total number of urban homeless and providing housing to all urban homeless.

news.title: Signature View Apartments residents & Delhi development body fail to break deadlock
news.para: DDA officials have given three options - redevelopment, buyback and swapping of flats - to the residents, who claim none of these is feasible. On Monday, a group of residents said they had met four DDA members and requested them to raise the matter in the next board meeting.

news.title: Papers forged, Haryana-RERA revokes real estate agent's registration
news.para: Under the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act 2016, it is mandatory for a real estate agent to obtain a Rera registration number.

news.title: Lodha Ventures-backed Bonito Designs targets over Rs 1,100 crore revenue in two years
news.para: The company’s revenue for the current financial year is estimated to be over Rs 275 crore while turning positive at EBITDA level and is on track to conclude the year with $100 million Annual Rate of Revenue (ARR).

news.title: Shapoorji Pallonji Group creates holding companies for infra & realty verticals to improve cash flows
news.para: The move will help improve operating cash flows since investments in long-lead businesses like infrastructure and real estate create timing mismatch, which puts debt burden on the balance sheet, officials said.

news.title: Noida: Details like OC, CC of housing projects now available online
news.para: Noida Authority's officer on special duty (Group Housing) Prasun Dwivedi said the section was made on the website on Monday and is aimed at promoting transparency and e-governance in public interest.

news.title: China Evergrande Group to detail debt restructure plan on March 22
news.para: Evergrande, which began one of China's biggest debt restructuring processes early last year, expects to sign a deal with general creditors by the end of March, with the restructuring to take effect from Oct 1, it added on Monday.

news.title: Raipur development body gives rebate on dues deposit by March 31
news.para: The allottees in Market, Boriyakhurd, Hirapur, Raipura and Transport Nagar Ranwabhata have the maximum outstanding amount under the old schemes. RDA chief executive officer Dharmesh Kumar Sahu said that the amount of surcharge is continuously increasing due to non-payment of regular payments in many projects.

news.title: OKAS looks to raise $500 million through its second real estate fund
news.para: The lead investor in OKAS' second real estate fund is New Investment Solutions (NIS), a Liechtenstein-based asset management company, that had led the earlier round in 2018.

news.title: More time to submit report on 'A' khatas in Bengaluru
news.para: Earlier, the civic agency had instructed them to prepare detailed reports on allegations that 'B' khata properties were illegally changed to 'A' khata. The reports were to be submitted to a review committee by 3pm on March 24.

news.title: Noida authority yet to get Rs 1,400 crore from 74 properties it has leased out
news.para: Those using the buildings and space deposited money in the beginning but stopped paying the rent later, the officials said, adding that notices had been sent to each of them.

news.title: Distribution delay as Pune civic body to reprint 4.5 lakh property tax bills
news.para: The new bills will be printed after the state government's decision to offer 40% tax discount for self-occupied properties. A notification will be soon issued.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body to roll out property ID cards from April 1
news.para: Interested residents can avail this card, which is similar to an ATM card, by paying a nominal charge of Rs 50. The basic purpose of this card is to give an ID to property holders of their records.

news.title: Chandigarh: Property tax bills to land in your mail from April
news.para: Taxpayers will be offered rebate — 20% for residential properties and 10% for commercial buildings — if they make the payment from April 1 to May 31. From June, defaulters will have to pay 25% penalty on the tax and 12% interest too.
